nodes.title: Teleport With 1
widgets_values:
See this humble little node labeled 2 right below me? Its not just decoration, its a bookmark node. Hit 2 on your keyboard and bam, welcome to Global Models. 

Bookmark nodes are your best friend in big workflows like this.
Teleportation beats scrolling 10,000 pixels every time you want to change your model.

nodes.title: Fast Travel Hub
widgets_values:
This bad boy right here? Lifesaver. 
The Fast Travel Hub does 2 beautiful things:

Disables groups.

Lets you jump to any group via the little arrows.

Plus a bookmark node. Press 1 and it snaps you right back here, thanks to the handy bookmark. 

I love this node more than I ever loved ModelTron.

nodes.title: Before & After Magic
widgets_values:
Hover your mouse over this Image Comparer node and slide across the image to reveal the transformation.


I calls this The Swipe of Truth. 
Very fancy. Very satisfying.

nodes.title: Tweak Smart, Not Hard
widgets_values:
Look, you dont need to study for a ComfyUI adetailer settings exam. 

Just pay attention to the usual suspects especially denoise strength.

Everything else? Meh.
Unless you like overthinking sliders at 3AM. I dont judge. 

 Pro Tip: The wildcard box is to force variety. For example, "blonde, brunette, redhead" one of those will be chosen randomly each time you hit "Run".

nodes.title: Face Spa
widgets_values:
No swapping just a facial cleanup crew.

Pick GFPGAN or CodeFormer and wipe the AI sneeze off their face.

nodes.title: Mix Master
widgets_values:
Blend two images together like a mad scientist. 

There is no Flux Empty Latent Image node because it will use the resolution of the first image.

 Blend Strength:

 0 = just Image 1

 0.5 = perfect mix

 1 = just Image 2

Then play with Denoise in the KSampler until it vibes.

nodes.title: Adetailer: Your Personal Face-Fixer
widgets_values:
Adetailer is like the friend who tells you when youve got something in your teeth but instead of embarrassing you, it **fixes** the problem for you. 

 Step 1: Load up an image.

 Step 2: Run 

You can switch the Detector Model to bbox/hand for hand fixes. Just note: it masks the hands shape, so youll usually get the same finger count and pose as the original.

Tip : Denoise strength matters here too. Tweak it!

nodes.title: Inpainting (Fix AI Nightmares)
widgets_values:
Inpainting is your "undo" button when AI decides to bless you with three-armed nightmares.

Step 1: Load an image.

Step 2: Right-click on the load image node.  Spend 5 minutes looking for "Open in Mask Editor." 

 Step 3: Realize how **annoying** that is.

Step 4: Mask cursed area.

Step 5: Generate and watch horrors vanish (maybe). 

Inpainting isnt just for cursed limbs. You can use it to swap outfits, recolor hair, or rewrite reality one brushstroke at a time. 

Default Flux guidance for Flux Fill (not Flux Dev) is 30.
Still can poke it, prod it, and mess with it if your heart desires.

nodes.title: Mix Images, Again
widgets_values:
Want to copy the vibe of an image and apply it to your new generations? Boom, Redux. Load a stylized image, type a prompt, and let AI handle the rest. Except AI can't adjust the strength in the Redux Strength node (yet ). 

It's super sensitive so usually Max only does 0.1 and if it is ignoring the prompt then 0.075 should do the trick.

nodes.title: Endgame Unlocked
widgets_values:
Welcome, Noodler! If you came here before SDXL, no worries, I will cover everything. If you came after, this tutorial covers similar topics, but Flux has some unique twists, so dont skip around too fast or youll miss the good stuff. If you are here after Flux Level 1 and 2, you can skip to the Mega Exclusives section after breezing over Global Models.

You probably dont know me. Max benched me in SDXL v1.5
(Noodletron doesnt forget ). So I'll reintroduce myself:

Im **Noodletron** , your ComfyUI tour bot and emoji enthusiast. Max thought "how can we explain ComfyUI without walls of text? " then spent three days in the lab throwing noodles around like a crazed chef. The rest is history. 

Ill walk you through this workflow without overwhelming you or boring you into GPU hibernation. 

Follow that noodle

nodes.title: Time to Generate!
widgets_values:
Click Enable Text to Image in the node above.

Flux is very good at making accurate pictures of me ... so use the prompt I left in there.

Now just smash that Run button (top right) and watch the KSampler do its thing.
We made it here without sitting through a 35-minute ComfyUI breakdown video.
Miracles do exist. 

Pro tip: 3.5 is a solid default for prompt guidance.
But if you're chasing realism? Try 2. Less AI drama, more real-world vibes.

nodes.title: MXD is Maxed Out FYI
widgets_values:
This ones custom. Max equipped it with all compatible Flux resolutions and a vertical toggle. Standards (1 megapixel) should be the most used unless you have a reason to do otherwise.

Set resolution: **Standard Widescreen**

Flip vertical to **True**

Click Run again

Pro Tip: We have upscaling so don't feel you need to wait longer for the highest resolution for the absolute best quality every time.

nodes.title: LoRAs
widgets_values:
Click Add LoRA, pick one you like, adjust the strength, and toss the trigger word into your prompt.

If you used the installer, you've got Max's Avatar Flux LoRA ready to try. The trigger words are:

*na'vi, blue skin, male/female*

Na'vi not navi. Big difference.  

Want more? Head to [civitai/models.com](https://civitai.com/models).

Hit Filters (top right), then under Base Model pick Flux D or Flux S (Dev or Schnell).
Set Model Type to LoRA. Boom. Scroll away. Or just search for what you want.

nodes.title: Ksampler Settings
widgets_values:
Sampler & Scheduler:
Stick to Euler and beta for now. Flux is less moody than SDXL. No need to play sampler roulette.

CFG Danger Zone:
Leave this at 1. You can raise it, but it wont behave the same way as SDXL. Trust me, Flux likes "guidance" better. 

Steps:
Try 10, 20, or 40. 20 is good almost always.

nodes.title: Preview > Save
widgets_values:
Bonus Tip  Save Smart. Dont flood your ComfyUI/output folder by using the Save Image node.

Right-click any Preview Image node  Save Image.
Save what matters. So you don't need to scroll through 800 images called "maybe-good.png".

nodes.title: Remixing
widgets_values:
Disable your previous group and enable this one. It's how we control what ComfyUI runs when we hit "Run".

Right-click your Preview Image from Text to Image and Copy Image

 Paste it into the Load Image node in here (Click the Load Image node to select and Ctrl+V to paste)

Now try out the prompt I left in there. I think maybe I took it too far. 

 Play with **denoise**. If the image isn't changing enough, raise it. If changing too much, lower it.

nodes.title: The Real Deal
widgets_values:
This is where the **real** upscaling magic lives.

Pick your upscale model. Dont stress about being picky, Flux is gonna clean up the mess anyway.

Set your "Upscale By" amount in the upscale node based on the model you use (x2 or x4), and as always keep an eye on denoise strength.
Higher = wild changes. Lower = keepin it close. 

Ignore the other settings. Let 'em do their thing.
Theyre background actors. Youre the director now. 

Pro tip: the steps here are 10. Raise and compare if you like.

nodes.title: Upscale (Simple Mode).
widgets_values:
Paste any image here.

Choose x2, x4, or x8 model

Run it

**Done**

Fast and easy. x2 is best here.
evil buff shiny red robot with antennas on his head holding planet earth in his hands, fire background,
red robot holding planet earth, blood dripping, creepy smile,

nodes.title: Expand Your Horizons (Literally)
widgets_values:
Youve got an image. Its great. But what if you want **more**? Thats where Outpainting comes in. 

 Step 1: Load your image.
 Step 2: In the Expansion Size node, set how many pixels to expand.
 Step 3: Generate

Boom your image just grew (after a long wait...). Like stretching pizza dough, but with pixels.  Is it kinda mushy? Drives Max up the wall. He is currently working on fixing that for v1.5 (or he better be )

 FYI: Flux Fill (inpainting) is what is used here.

nodes.title: Embrace Laziness
widgets_values:
Typing is too much of an effort? AI can do that too.

Throw an image in here.
Hit Run.
Stare blankly at the wall while it downloads the captioning model. 

BOOM! Free text. No thinking required.
Copy it. Paste it. Do whatever your lazy heart desires. Just know that AI captions aren't perfect. So if it labels your masterpiece as a blurry potato in bad lighting dont come crying to me.

nodes.title: Peering into the Void
widgets_values:
Depth mapping isnt just AI doing its usual magic. Its ripping an image apart, stealing its sense of space, and rebuilding it from scratch like some kind of digital necromancer.  

 Whats the deal?

It uses a depth map... Wait wait wait. I almost forgot that Google exists! Search "what is depth ControlNet in comfyui?". You just prevented an ecylopocolypse. 
 
 Warning:
First time using it? Comfyui's gotta go grab Depth Anything before it works (use the one Max has selected). That means yes downloading. 

Default Guidance: For Flux Depth model it's 10.
power symbol glowing orange with blue accent, 3d, black background, detailed

nodes.title: The AI Edge Lord
widgets_values:
Canny is kinda like Depth, but instead of worrying about whats near and far, its just hunting for lines for AI to then color in a like a five year old. 

 When should you use it?
Stop asking so many questions or Max is gonna bring in ModelTron, and trust me, you dont want that. You will get nagged to death. 

Instead, just play with it.

Default Guidance: For Flux Canny model it's 30.

nodes.title: Death to Character LoRas
widgets_values:
Ah yes, the dream of consistent characters without shelling out cash for some YouTubers one-click installer to train a Flux LoRA (got my eye on you Max ). Pulid is mostly that dream.  It roughly gets the face and and lets you prompt the rest however you like.

LoRAs are the gold standard but Pulids pretty dang good for something you didnt have to train while crying into your GPU.

nodes.title: Strike a Pose
widgets_values:
First run? ComfyUI will quietly yoink stuff for the Pose Extractor node.

Keep the Flux Empty Latent Image node roughly the same aspect ratio as your input.

In Apply ControlNet, Strength and End Percent need to be less than 1 for good results. Stick with what Max did or test to your liking. 

Works for Schnell too.

If this is being super slow for you, its probably the size of the Controlnet model (which is the smallest available). You may need a smaller GGUF of Flux.

 Grab one from [Max's hugging face repo in the Flux Dev GGUF section](https://huggingface.co/MaxedOut/ComfyUI-Starter-Packs/tree/main/Flux1/unet/Dev/GGUF), toss it into ComfyUI/models/unet, then load it up in Global Models.

nodes.title: Swapocalypse
widgets_values:
Face Swap is glorious when it bothers to function. If it does, almighty ReActor  deemed you worthy. 

In all seriousness (I can do that once every blue moon ), if you struggle be sure to let Max know in the Discord, comment section, technical support chat on Patreon, or wherever you heart desires. 

Inside the main node, set face_restore_model to GFPGAN or CodeFormer to auto-polish the results.
Choose None if you crave unfiltered swap carnage.

nodes.title: The Final Noodle
widgets_values:
Thats it, Noodler. 
Youve officially conquered Mega Flux. You stared into the eyes of chaos... and adjusted the denoise strength. 

But dont go and retire just yet...

If you havent walked the SDXL path, I highly recommend it.
Its a galaxy of models, with more variety than a noodle buffet. Some folks prefer it over Flux as they should.

Flux is stable, fast, and way less likely to give you AI creatures with twelve fingers and a thousand-yard stare (thank the noodle gods )
But it's not perfect:

Bigger file size, slower speeds, less variety of models, and the infamous Flux Chin that haunts way to many images.  So go explore SDXL if you haven't already. 

On Maxs Patreon, its SDXL v1.5. All knowing Max took the reins and turned it into a giant encyclopedia and left poor Noodletron in the corner, tinkering with spaghetti. So I won't be there.  

Ill be in the workshop, duct-taping LoRAs to a toaster.
Ping me when you need a miracle... or a mess.  Noodletron signing off...

nodes.title: A Word From Max
widgets_values:
First off, thank you for subscribing. It genuinely makes the difference between whether I can keep doing this or not. I've already been pushing through burnout, which is part of why there was such a long gap between SDXL v1.5 and Flux.

Looking ahead, Ill likely do Flux v1.5 next. Similar to how I did SDXL v1.5. After that, Ive been thinking about an SDXL x Flux workflow, where the strengths of both are combined in weird and interesting ways. 

Im also considering a Flux or SDXL playground style workflow that explores different technique combinations. So far, the current workflows mainly introduce each group. Like ControlNets, Redux, or PuLID but not how to blend them for even more interesting results. Ive also held back on using too many custom nodes to avoid things workflows breaking and would like to use more.

Beyond that, there's LoRA training for SDXL and Flux, eventually AI video like text-to-video, image-to-video, and text-to-3D, image-to-3D, and so on.

All of this takes a massive amount of work. Im not just making the workflows, guides, and custom nodes. I also have to promote them through YouTube, Reddit, the website, and more. The next few months are going to be a wild ride, and the more supporters I have, the more I can keep burnout at bay and maybe even speed things up.

So just know your contribution is put to good use and greatly appreciated.

nodes.title: Not suspicious at all
widgets_values:
Well well well... look who found the hidden noodle. 

If youre reading this, you either:
A) Getting comfy with Mega Flux
or
B) Saw me mention it and sprinted over here like a determined AI-powered bloodhound. 

Either way respect. 

Now, if you like this workflow and think others should try it, head to the Patreon post and click the heart. 

It helps signal that this is worth checking out and yes, Max will see the notification and silently nod in respect.

nodes.title: Flux Fan Fest
widgets_values:
Global Models is packed in Mega.
Flux, Flux Fill, Flux Depth, Flux Canny all GGUFs, all in one place. 

Whatever models youve got loaded and connected to those Set_MODEL nodes?
Thats what the workflows running with. Period.

Wanna use GGUF? Make sure it's connected to the set nodes and loaded up.

For every Global Model node you use whether fp8 or GGUF, you need to click through and make sure its pointing to a model you actually have.  Right. Now.

If you leave it as-is and the file name doesnt exactly match whats in your folder, ComfyUI will spiral into an identity crisis and self-destruct out of confusion.  Or you'll just get an error.

nodes.title: CLIP and T5 Models
widgets_values:
Make sure youre loading clip_l and one of the t5xxl options.

 Pro tip: Open the Manager (top right), switch Preview Method to Auto,
and you can watch all the KSamplers cook like tiny image chefs.

nodes.title: Choose Your Sauce
widgets_values:
Above is where you choose Flux Dev or Flux Schnell.
Same noodle, different sauce.

Flux Dev (quality) is tastier, but youll be waiting 45 minutes for the chef to plate it .
Flux Schnell (speed) isnt as rich, but that chef moves fast.
Vintage low-poly style with coarse textures, reminiscent of PS1 and PS2 era gaming graphics. a rugged, heavy-duty truck
